{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.31",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 31,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 31",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 31 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:1",
      "text": "“ I made a covenant with my eyes; how then should I look lustfully at a young woman?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:2",
      "text": "For what is the portion from God above, and the heritage from the Almighty on high?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:3",
      "text": "Is it not calamity to the unrighteous, and disaster to the workers of iniquity?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:4",
      "text": "Doesn’t he see my ways, and count all my steps?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:5",
      "text": "“If I have walked with falsehood, and my foot has hurried to deceit",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:6",
      "text": "(let me be weighed in an even balance, that God may know my integrity);",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:7",
      "text": "if my step has turned out of the way, if my heart walked after my eyes, if any defilement has stuck to my hands,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:8",
      "text": "then let me sow, and let another eat. Yes, let the produce of my field be rooted out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:9",
      "text": "“If my heart has been enticed to a woman, and I have laid wait at my neighbor ’s door,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:10",
      "text": "then let my wife grind for another, and let others sleep with her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:11",
      "text": "For that would be a heinous crime. Yes, it would be an iniquity to be punished by the judges,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:12",
      "text": "for it is a fire that consumes to destruction, and would root out all my increase.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:13",
      "text": "“If I have despised the cause of my male servant or of my female servant, when they contended with me,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:14",
      "text": "what then will I do when God rises up? When he visits, what will I answer him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:15",
      "text": "Didn’t he who made me in the womb make him? Didn’t one fashion us in the womb?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:16",
      "text": "“If I have withheld the poor from their desire, or have caused the eyes of the widow to fail,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:17",
      "text": "or have eaten my morsel alone, and the fatherless has not eaten of it",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:18",
      "text": "(no, from my youth he grew up with me as with a father, I have guided her from my mother’s womb);",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:19",
      "text": "if I have seen any perish for want of clothing, or that the needy had no covering;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:20",
      "text": "if his heart hasn’t blessed me, if he hasn’t been warmed with my sheep ’s fleece;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:21",
      "text": "if I have lifted up my hand against the fatherless, because I saw my help in the gate;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:22",
      "text": "then let my shoulder fall from the shoulder blade, and my arm be broken from the bone.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:23",
      "text": "For calamity from God is a terror to me. Because of his majesty, I can do nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:24",
      "text": "“ If I have made gold my hope, and have said to the fine gold, ‘ You are my confidence;’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:25",
      "text": "If I have rejoiced because my wealth was great, and because my hand had gotten much;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:26",
      "text": "if I have seen the sun when it shined, or the moon moving in splendor,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:27",
      "text": "and my heart has been secretly enticed, and my hand threw a kiss from my mouth;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:28",
      "text": "this also would be an iniquity to be punished by the judges, for I would have denied the God who is above.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:29",
      "text": "“ If I have rejoiced at the destruction of him who hated me, or lifted up myself when evil found him",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:30",
      "text": "(I have certainly not allowed my mouth to sin by asking his life with a curse);",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:31",
      "text": "if the men of my tent have not said, ‘ Who can find one who has not been filled with his meat?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:32",
      "text": "(the foreigner has not camped in the street, but I have opened my doors to the traveler);",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:33",
      "text": "if like Adam I have covered my transgressions, by hiding my iniquity in my heart,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:34",
      "text": "because I feared the great multitude, and the contempt of families terrified me, so that I kept silence, and didn’t go out of the door —",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:35",
      "text": "oh that I had one to hear me! Behold, here is my signature! Let the Almighty answer me! Let the accuser write my indictment!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.36",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:36",
      "text": "Surely I would carry it on my shoulder, and I would bind it to me as a crown.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.37",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:37",
      "text": "I would declare to him the number of my steps. I would go near to him like a prince.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.38",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:38",
      "text": "If my land cries out against me, and its furrows weep together;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.39",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:39",
      "text": "if I have eaten its fruits without money, or have caused its owners to lose their life,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.31.40",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:40",
      "text": "let briers grow instead of wheat, and stinkweed instead of barley.” The words of Job are ended.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
